    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and documented; the overall evidence body — comprising N=11 specimens across two independent laboratories with E/uval values well below 1.96 for all three QoIs — provides sufficient confidence for a Medium assurance level decision. The FEA modeling framework is accepted for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
